               <p>265. <persName id="def1-265-18431127" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-265-18431127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-265-18431127" type="age" value="37"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-265-18431127" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-265-18431127" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MICHAEL SMITH</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18431127-265-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18431127-265-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18431127-265-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for uttering counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. BODKIN</hi> and <hi rend="smallCaps">ESPINASSE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1420" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1420" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1420" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1420" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN COOPER</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">licensed victualler, Deptford.</hi> On Sunday afternoon, the 12th of Nov., the prisoner came to my house for a glass of gin, which came to 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he gave me a half-crown—I gave him change, and he left—I put the half-crown in the till—I am sure there was no other there—in less than five minutes I looked at it again—no one had been to the till in the mean time—I found it was bad—I marked it and put it on the shelf—no one knew where it was—it remained there till Lovell came—on the 20th I gave it him from the same place—I am sure the prisoner is the man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I got a little drink and was not aware of it, <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> He was sober.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1421" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1421" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1421" type="surname" value="LOVELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1421" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>BENJAMIN LOVELL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant R</hi> 15.) On the 20th of Nov. I received this half-crown from Cooper—I took the prisoner in High-street, Deptford—he said he knew nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1422" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1422" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1422" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1422" type="given" value="THOMAS JOSEPH"></interp>THOMAS JOSEPH HUNT</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Fox, King-street, Deptford. On the 18th of Nov., a little after nine at night, the prisoner came for a glass of gin—he gave me half-a-crown—I saw it was bad—I said, "This is a bad one"—he said, "If so, I took it of my master in part of wages"—he then gave me a good one—I gave him change—I retained the bad one and sent for a policeman, marked it in his presence, and gave it him—he took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1423" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1423" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1423" type="surname" value="DEAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1423" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES DEAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 319.) I was called to Hunt's, and took the prisoner in charge—I received a half-crown from Mr. Hunt, which he marked—I afterwards gave it to the inspector—the charge was not pressed, and the prisoner was let go.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
